awd_titl_txt: Analytical Model of Cable-Stayed Bridge Nonlinear Dynamics  for Mitigation of Extreme Load Effects
awd_abstract_narration: The project will develop and implement a                                        computational nonlinear mode superposition                                      algorithm in a parallel computing                                               environment, based on Duffing's principle of                                    instantaneous mode superposition.  This                                         algorithm will be applied to cable-stayed                                       bridges, which exhibits geometric                                               nonlinearities due to cable sag, axial-                                         flexural interaction, and inherently large                                      displacements.  These nonlinearities are most                                   pronounced in the partially-constructed                                         stage.  The resulting applications will be                                      used to understand the complex interactions                                     of earthquakes, extreme winds and traffic                                       forces and their induced structural dynamic                                     response.  The research will provide the                                        practicing and research engineers with a tool                                   that will help in better understanding                                          nonlinear dynamic response behavior of large                                    structures such as cable-stayed bridges.
